Plugins
=======

stawebg/plugins/... or data/plugins/...

config:
    "plugins":
    {
        "TEST1":                -> %PLUGIN_TEST1%
        {
            "type": "test",     -> test.py
            "c1": 4,            -> config
            "c2": "hiafasf"
        },
        "TEST2":
        {
            "type": "test",
            "c1": 10,
            "c2": "hi"
        }
    }

    mapping
    plugin must be registered before config is parsed -> extend config description

index of available plugins (like markup languages)

plugin can request layout files (check for all registered plugins)

replace keywords: find keyword -> request plugin content -> replace keyword

plugin can create Page or OtherFile
    -> OtherFile is copy of file or (NEW) a plaintext file

plugin class -> can be extended
    -> simple access to layout...
    -> create Page
    -> create OtherFile
